WEBVTT

00:00:00.780 --> 00:00:07.339
Now, this word picture of someone being stumbled is quite vivid, isn't it?

00:00:07.339 --> 00:00:09.419
We've all seen someone stumbled.

00:00:09.419 --> 00:00:16.820
In fact, we've all stumbled ourselves at times, and there are varying degrees of consequences.

00:00:16.820 --> 00:00:23.859
For example, a person can stumble, quickly recover, and continue almost uneventfully down

00:00:23.859 --> 00:00:25.500
the path.

00:00:25.500 --> 00:00:32.740
There are a person can stumble, fall, break a bone, eventually they recover, but only

00:00:32.740 --> 00:00:35.299
after extensive therapy.

00:00:35.299 --> 00:00:44.259
Then again, a person can stumble, fall, hit his head, never recover, becoming a casualty.

00:00:44.259 --> 00:00:49.219
Well the situation is similar when one is stumbled spiritually.

00:00:49.219 --> 00:00:56.700
We can recover quickly, maybe recover over time, or he may never recover, becoming a

00:00:56.700 --> 00:00:59.219
spiritual casualty.

00:00:59.219 --> 00:01:04.859
So we can not know the ultimate outcome for someone who is stumbled.

00:01:04.859 --> 00:01:11.739
So no wonder we're cautioned to be very careful to never be any cause for stumbling.

00:01:11.739 --> 00:01:19.579
Turn up to Matthew chapter 18, and here's an especially powerful scripture in this regard.

00:01:19.579 --> 00:01:25.819
Matthew 18 verse 6, Jesus says, but whoever stumbles one of these little ones who have faith

00:01:25.819 --> 00:01:32.099
in me, it would be better for him to have hung around his neck a millstone that is turned

00:01:32.099 --> 00:01:38.420
by a donkey and a bee sunk in the open sea.

00:01:38.420 --> 00:01:45.980
Well with graphic language, Jesus describes how that if we cause someone to become a spiritual

00:01:45.980 --> 00:01:51.620
casualty, we could actually bring eternal doom upon ourselves.

00:01:51.620 --> 00:01:57.500
But now here's a question, what could we do to cause someone to stumble?

00:01:57.500 --> 00:02:03.099
Well interestingly there are several similarities between causing someone to stumble physically

00:02:03.099 --> 00:02:06.019
and causing someone to stumble spiritually.

00:02:06.019 --> 00:02:08.379
Let us discuss three.

00:02:08.379 --> 00:02:15.699
Now one, pushing someone could cause them to stumble, especially if they're on uneven

00:02:15.699 --> 00:02:18.300
terrain if you think about it.

00:02:18.300 --> 00:02:22.460
And this is true physically, spiritually.

00:02:22.460 --> 00:02:26.699
But think about Jehovah for a moment, he could push any of us, couldn't he?

00:02:26.699 --> 00:02:28.900
He could force us to serve him.

00:02:28.900 --> 00:02:32.740
He certainly has the power, but he never uses it that way.

00:02:32.740 --> 00:02:35.900
Instead he invites, he encourages.

00:02:35.900 --> 00:02:40.620
And he explains the blessings, the curses, depending upon how we decide.

00:02:40.620 --> 00:02:42.180
But it's up to us, isn't it?

00:02:42.180 --> 00:02:51.419
For example, Isaiah 48, 18, Jehovah says, if only you would pay attention to my commandments,

00:02:51.419 --> 00:02:58.500
then your peace would become like a river and your righteousness like the waves of the

00:02:58.500 --> 00:02:59.740
sea.

00:02:59.740 --> 00:03:03.099
He's teaching, but not forcing.

00:03:03.099 --> 00:03:06.699
Now think about it, if Jehovah doesn't force, he doesn't want us to force either, does

00:03:06.699 --> 00:03:07.699
he?

00:03:07.699 --> 00:03:13.219
